records.addlTxt:
Defendant Matthew J Larson in court with attorney Anna M Kees.  
Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was sworn and examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.   

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 

The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 5 YEARS with credit for 4 days. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 1/2  YEARS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 1/2 YEARS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 4 YEARS with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION (if revoked):
*Serve 12 months in the House of Correction with release for employment- good time allowed;
*Obtain Mental Health evaluation and complete any follow-up care/treatment;
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens- no controlled substances unless prescribed for mental health treatment by physician licensed in WI;
*Seek/maintain full time employment;
*Participate in job/vocational training;
*Participate in Parenting counseling;
*Participate in Cognitive Thinking Intervention counseling;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;

The Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of $1000.00 plus all mandatory costs, penalties, surcharges, including $50.00 ignition interlock surcharge by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Court ordered AODA assessment and Driver's Safety Plan; be in full compliance with plan before license reinstated.  Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for a period of 2 years.  Court ordered defendant restricted to operation of vehicles equipped with an ignition interlock device for 2 years.  If revoked, the Court ordered that all financial obligations be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Appeal rights given.  Defendant remanded and taken into custody. *jury trial date of 7-08-15 removed from the calendar at this time*

Filed:
-Driver Assessment and Driver Safety Plan;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-First Judicial District OWI Sentencing Guidelines;
-Plea Agreement;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
-Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence- copy to defendant.
